      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-07-11</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-05-04T18:43:31Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Transparency and Accountability for Business Standards Act </b></p> <p>This bill requires a&nbsp;federal banking agency to&nbsp;publish for notice and comment: (1)&nbsp;the agency's rationale for,&nbsp;and cost-benefit analysis regarding, the adoption of any prudential regulation that is substantively more stringent than a corresponding international prudential standard; and (2) a proposal for, or the agency's rationale for not proposing, the repeal or amendment of any&nbsp;prudential regulation that is effectively superseded by the implementation of an international prudential standard.</p>  <p>A federal banking agency must issue a report regarding any such final rule issued before the bill's enactment and on or after January 1, 2007.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
